service: WorkSpaces Web is a low cost, fully managed WorkSpace built specifically to facilitate secure, web-based workloads. WorkSpaces Web makes it easy for customers to safely provide their employees with access to internal websites and SaaS web applications without the administrative burden of appliances or specialized client software. WorkSpaces Web provides simple policy tools tailored for user interactions, while offloading common tasks like capacity management, scaling, and maintaining browser images.

operations.AssociateBrowserSettings: Associates a browser settings resource with a web portal.
operations.AssociateNetworkSettings: Associates a network settings resource with a web portal.
operations.AssociateTrustStore: Associates a trust store with a web portal.
operations.AssociateUserSettings: Associates a user settings resource with a web portal.
operations.CreateBrowserSettings: Creates a browser settings resource that can be associated with a web portal. Once associated with a web portal, browser settings control how the browser will behave once a user starts a streaming session for the web portal.
operations.CreateIdentityProvider: Creates an identity provider resource that is then associated with a web portal.
operations.CreateNetworkSettings: Creates a network settings resource that can be associated with a web portal. Once associated with a web portal, network settings define how streaming instances will connect with your specified VPC.
operations.CreateTrustStore: Creates a trust store that can be associated with a web portal. A trust store contains certificate authority (CA) certificates. Once associated with a web portal, the browser in a streaming session will recognize certificates that have been issued using any of the CAs in the trust store. If your organization has internal websites that use certificates issued by private CAs, you should add the private CA certificate to the trust store.
operations.CreateUserSettings: Creates a user settings resource that can be associated with a web portal. Once associated with a web portal, user settings control how users can transfer data between a streaming session and the their local devices.
operations.DisassociateBrowserSettings: Disassociates browser settings from a web portal.
operations.DisassociateNetworkSettings: Disassociates network settings from a web portal.
operations.DisassociateTrustStore: Disassociates a trust store from a web portal.
operations.DisassociateUserSettings: Disassociates user settings from a web portal.
operations.ListIdentityProviders: Retrieves a list of identity providers for a specific web portal.
operations.ListTagsForResource: Retrieves a list of tags for a resource.
operations.ListTrustStoreCertificates: Retrieves a list of trust store certificates.
operations.TagResource: Adds or overwrites one or more tags for the specified resource.
operations.UntagResource: Removes one or more tags from the specified resource.

refs.CreateIdentityProviderRequest$identityPr:
The identity provider details. The following list describes the provider detail keys for each identity provider type.

  • For Google and Login with Amazon:

    • client_id

    • client_secret

    • authorize_scopes

  • For Facebook:

    • client_id

    • client_secret

    • authorize_scopes

    • api_version

  • For Sign in with Apple:

    • client_id

    • team_id

    • key_id

    • private_key

    • authorize_scopes

  • For OIDC providers:

    • client_id

    • client_secret

    • attributes_request_method

    • oidc_issuer

    • authorize_scopes

    • authorize_url if not available from discovery URL specified by oidc_issuer key

    • token_url if not available from discovery URL specified by oidc_issuer key

    • attributes_url if not available from discovery URL specified by oidc_issuer key

    • jwks_uri if not available from discovery URL specified by oidc_issuer key

  • For SAML providers:

    • MetadataFile OR MetadataURL

    • IDPSignout optional
